  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quality Control Inspector",
  "description": "<p>Primary Responsibility:</p><p>1. Perform Visual Inspection using Baroscopic technique. Perform NDT in PT, UT, and MT methods. Calibrate equipment. Interpret weld profile for acceptance. Prepare inspection reports.</p><p>2. View and interpret radiograph films, evaluate discontinuities.</p><p>3. Perform Inspection at shop facilities and worksites, on blasting, painting works, galvanizing.</p><p>4. Check weld joint preparations, fit-up alignment, dimensional tolerances, and visual check on weld.</p><p>5. Interpret construction and technical drawings, prepare piping weld maps.</p><p>6. Communicate the engineering/technical/quality requirement to the direct workforce who are on the job.</p><p>7. Verify that incoming materials meet the requirement.</p><p>8. Supervise piping fabrication, structural fabrication, Piping installation, testing, and handover to customer with required project documentation.</p><p>installation works per ASME and other relevant codes.</p><p>9. Follow-up on corrective action of non-conforming products.</p><p>10. Conduct welding procedures qualification tests and welders’ performance qualification tests.</p><p>11. Prepare Test Plans, NDT, and project specific procedures.</p><p>12. Implement and monitor proper storage, handling and usage of welding equipment and welding filter rods.</p><p>Additional Responsibility:</p><p>1. Assign daily job to the workers, monitor welding progress, prepare daily progress report.</p><p>2. Handle purchasing of materials and consumable.</p><p>3. Conduct tool box talk, co-ordinate permit-to work system with client, monitor timely start-work</p><p>4. Monitor safe work practice during work execution, Participate in Risk Assessment preparation and implementation.</p><p>Qualification and experience:</p><p>1. Bachelor degree in Engineering/Arts/Business/Administration</p><p>2. Weld Visual Inspector, NDT Certification</p><p>3. Minimum 8 years of hands-on experience with similar projects</p><p>4. Candidates not meeting above qualification requirement but having more than 10 years of experience in above filed of work, may be considered.</p>",
